  year         = {2013},
  url          = {https://curia.europa.eu/juris/liste.jsf?num=C-335/11},
  abstract      = {HK Danmark acting on behalf of Jette Ring v. Dansk almennyttigt Boligselskab and HK Danmark acting on behalf of Lone Skouboe Werge v. Dansk Arbejdsgiverforening acting on behalf of Pro Display A/S (Joined Cases C-335/11 and C-337/11, Second Chamber, 11 April 2013). Ms Ring suffered from chronic back pain and osteoarthritis changes in the lumbar vertebrae; Ms Skouboe Werge suffered whiplash from a traffic accident. Both were dismissed under a Danish provision permitting dismissal with reduced notice for employees on sick leave for 120 days in 12 months. The CJEU further developed its case law on disability under Directive 2000/78/EC in light of the UN CRPD, holding that a curable or incurable illness entailing a physical, mental or psychological limitation may be assimilated to a disability if it prevents full and effective participation in professional life on equal terms, and that a reduction in working hours may constitute a reasonable accommodation measure.},
  note         = {Aff. jointes C-335/11 et C-337/11, 11 avril 2013 --- This ruling expands the scope of reasonable accommodation obligations for staff and students with chronic conditions or long-term health impairments.},
