  abstract      = {This page describes three types of IP address ranges used on the University Data Network (UDN). Global (public) addresses are ranges routed directly between the UDN and the public internet, split into inside addresses considered part of the University and outside addresses not considered University ranges. UDN-local (private) addresses are routed within the UDN but translated to global addresses when exiting, ideal for client-only devices where direct inbound connections are not possible. Institution-local (private) addresses are reserved for use internally by institutions. The page strongly recommends that IP addresses are not used as a method of access control, as users on the network may include visitors, contractors, and affiliated organisations.},
