  abstract     = {The UK's national technical authority for cyber security, part of GCHQ, providing guidance, incident response and threat intelligence. Under the Network and Information Systems Regulations 2018 the NCSC performs the functions of the single point of contact (SPOC) and the national computer security incident response team (CSIRT), offering technical advice to competent authorities. For universities the NCSC publishes the Cyber Assessment Framework and sector guidance and operates the channels through which cyber incidents feed national situational awareness; it is the technical-authority counterpart to the legal competent authorities (ICO and sector regulators).},
